President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to appoint James E. Hutton as an Assistant Secretary of Veterans Affairs for Public and Intergovernmental Affairs. Hutton is currently serving as the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of Veterans Affairs. He has previously held positions such as Executive Director of Public Affairs and Director of Media Relations at the VA, as well as the Chief Communication and Engagement Officer for Tragedy Assistance Program for Survivors. Hutton has also served for almost 27 years as an active duty officer in the United States Army, retiring as a colonel. He holds multiple degrees, including a Bachelor of Science degree from Oklahoma State University, a Master of Arts degree from Webster University, and a Master of Science degree from the National Defense University's National War College. Hutton has received various military awards, including the Legion of Merit, three Bronze Star Medals, and two Defense Meritorious Service Medals.